{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QbGoM2VRHovZAHx1Qdr16n","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - Prometheus has a ClusterRole that allows it to get/list/watch nodes, services, endpoints, pods, and configmaps across the cluster. This should allow it to discover and scrape the CockroachDB service in the cockroachdb namespace.\n\nHowever, I also need to make sure the Prometheus operator can read ServiceMonitors in the cockroachdb namespace. Let me check if the prometheus-operator has the necessary permissions.\n\nActually, the key thing is:\n1. The Prometheus CR is configured with `serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector.matchNames: [\"cockroachdb\"]` - so it will look for ServiceMonitors in the `cockroachdb` namespace ✓\n2. The ServiceMonitor is in the `cockroachdb` namespace and selects CockroachDB services by label ✓\n3. The endpoint is configured to scrape `/_status/vars` on port 8080 ✓\n4. The Prometheus service account has the necessary ClusterRole permissions ✓\n\nNow I should check the Prometheus targets via its API to verify it's actually picking up the CockroachDB endpoints.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":343,"cache_read_input_tokens":32869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":343},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14d4c799-50da-4ca3-800f-5cba91dc7e37","uuid":"009b5aa5-c98b-430a-9fd2-fe854aebdccc","request_id":"req_011CcQA8HVUdu31XdKyHk3fY"}
